{"title":"Review: First Rides on Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X Gravel Tire’s New Rubber","link":"https://bikerumor.com/first-look-maxxis-reaver-45mm-hypr-x-gravel-tires/","date":1744657200000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-logo-1536x864.webp\" width=\"1536\" height=\"864\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X logo\" /></p>\n<p>Maxxis has been quietly crushing it in the gravel game for a while now, but they just gave their lineup a serious shot of go-fast juice. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/new-maxxis-hypr-x-compound-gravel-tires/\" target=\"_blank\">Meet HYPR-X, the new rubber compound</a> blending the best bits of Maxxis road-focused HYPR and mountain-bike-speed-demon MaxxSpeed formulas. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The result of the updated HYPR-X compound? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>A gravel compound that promises to roll faster, grip harder, and last longer—without turning your legs into mashed potatoes. We pushed the new Maxxis Reaver HYPR-X through the gravel paces, and the future is promising!</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Maxxis Reaver gravel tire, now in 45mm with HYPR-X rubber</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a><figcaption><em>(All photos / Jordan Villella)</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Maxxis says the HYPR-X rubber update cuts rolling resistance by 25% and boosts cornering grip by 19%. But wait, there’s more. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Maxxis also upgraded the casing—still 120 TPI, but now with a tougher nylon fabric for more durability and a longer tread life. EXO sidewall protection is still part of the package, because sharp rocks and angry gravel don’t care how fast you’re going.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And yes — everything is tubeless-ready, because it’s 2025 and we’re civilized.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>A New Maxxis Look</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-lgoto-heder--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-lgoto-heder--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X lgoto heder\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-lgoto-heder--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-lgoto-heder--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-lgoto-heder--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-lgoto-heder--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-lgoto-heder--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-lgoto-heder--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-lgoto-heder--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Maxxis branding gets refreshed with simplified gray-and-orange hot patches. Plus, Maxxis is ditching plastic packaging in favor of recyclable paper sleeves, so your tire upgrade doesn’t come with an environmental guilt trip.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-side-knob--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-side-knob--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X side knob\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-side-knob--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-side-knob--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-side-knob--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-side-knob--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-side-knob--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-side-knob--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-side-knob--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new HYPR-X versions of this semi-slick Reaver and teh slightly knobbier Rambler will first be available in 700x45c, with more sizes trickling in over the next few months. Almost certainly a 40mm version, probably a 50mm, and maybe even something like some 55mm tires, too?</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Then, the beefier Ravager and the slick Receptor will get their own upgrades later in 2025.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Riding Impressions: Maxxis Reaver HYPR-X 45mm</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-full-bike--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-full-bike--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-full-bike--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-full-bike--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-full-bike--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-full-bike--120x67.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-full-bike--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-full-bike--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-full-bike--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>When I first covered the launch of the Maxxis Reaver <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/reaver-is-maxxis-fastest-pure-gravel-tire-to-date/\" target=\"_blank\">back in 2023</a>, it was all about speed. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Billed as Maxxis’ fastest pure gravel tire at the time, the Reaver was a purpose-built race machine—minimal knobs, file-tread centerline, low weight, and maximum speed on smoother gravel tracks. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But the new HYPR-X compound? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s aiming to take that legacy of speed and stretch it into chunkier, rowdier terrain without giving up what made the Reaver so fast in the first place.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>HYPR-X Rubber Advantage</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-top-rider-tread--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-top-rider-tread--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X top rider tread\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-top-rider-tread--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-top-rider-tread--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-top-rider-tread--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-top-rider-tread--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-top-rider-tread--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-top-rider-tread--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-top-rider-tread--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>With HYPR-X, Maxxis is blending its best road and MTB race tech—specifically, the low-rolling-resistance HYPR compound from its road line and the grippy MaxxSpeed compound from its XC MTB tires. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-tread-top-scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-tread-top-scaled.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X tread top\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-tread-top-scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-tread-top-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-tread-top-1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-tread-top-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-tread-top-768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-tread-top-2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-tread-top-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The result is a gravel tire compound that rolls <em>much</em> faster than expected for something that also bites this hard in corners. Maxxis makes those 25% less rolling resistance and 19% better cornering traction claims, compared to their previous ‘Dual’ compound. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>And honestly, it feels about right out on the trail. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Actual weight, a bit more than before</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-weight--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"864\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-weight--1536x864.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X weight\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-weight--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-weight--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-weight--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-weight--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-weight--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-weight--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-compair-weight--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"864\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-compair-weight--1536x864.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X compair weight\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-compair-weight--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-compair-weight--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-compair-weight--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-compair-weight--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-compair-weight--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-compair-weight--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new compound and updated casing construction seems to add a slight bit of weight, 17g on our scales, compared to the previous version in a 45mm.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Supple &amp; Fast </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-front--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-front--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X front\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-front--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-front--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-front--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-front--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-front--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-front--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-front--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>But the real story here isn’t just in the numbers—it’s in how the HYPR-X tires ride, especially on the kind of chunky, hard-packed rocks that many of us call “gravel.” In our testing so far, the updated Reaver in the new 700x45c size (the first to launch) feels like a welcome evolution: still light and fast, but wide enough to keep you composed on washboard, rocky descents, and unexpected trail detours.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you found the original Reaver a little too roadie for your backcountry ambitions, these new versions bring the volume and the grip to match more adventurous riding.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>And of course, adding this rubber to the full-knob Rambler will give you even more confidence off-the-beaten-track now, too.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Updated EXO Casing</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-inside--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-inside--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X inside\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-inside--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-inside--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-inside--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-inside--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-inside--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-inside--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-inside--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The updated 120 TPI casing is another quiet win. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Maxxis says they’ve used a stronger nylon inside that ups durability without losing suppleness. Paired with EXO sidewall protection and tubeless-ready design, these tires hold up under hard riding but still conform nicely over roots and loose terrain (no flats yet!).</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-packaging--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-packaging--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X packaging\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-packaging--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-packaging--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-packaging--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-packaging--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-packaging--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-packaging--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-packaging--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Aesthetically, they’ve also cleaned things up with subtle gray/orange hot patches and recyclable packaging. That last bit might not win races, but hey—it feels good to see a brand reduce plastic while upgrading performance.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-both--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-both--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X both\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-both--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-both--297x223.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-both--1536x1152.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-both--120x90.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-both--768x576.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-both--2048x1536.webp 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Compared to the original Reaver I tested, these new HYPR-X versions still feel fast—maybe not quite as zippy on pavement—but far more confidence-inspiring when the gravel gets aggressive and loose. They’re for riders who want a tire that doesn’t force a trade-off between speed and trail-readiness. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>In that way, the HYPR-X tires split the difference between pure gravel race rubber and a lightweight XC tire—and that’s a very sweet spot to hit.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>What’s next for Maxxis gravel?</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-close-up--scaled.webp\"><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1440\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-close-up--scaled.webp\" alt=\"Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X close up\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-close-up--scaled.webp 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-close-up--297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-close-up--1536x864.webp 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-close-up--120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-close-up--768x432.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-close-up--2048x1152.webp 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/Maxxis-Reaver-45mm-HYPR-X-close-up--1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Expect more sizes to drop throughout the year, with the Ravager and Receptor also getting the HYPR-X makeover soon. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>But if you’re the kind of rider who mixes racing with adventuring, or wants one tire that can handle the fast lines <em>and</em> the sketchy ones, any of these upgraded Maxxis tires are worth a serious look.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://shop.maxxis.com/collections/gravel-adventure\" target=\"_blank\">Maxxis.com</a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/first-look-maxxis-reaver-45mm-hypr-x-gravel-tires/\">Review: First Rides on Maxxis Reaver 45mm HYPR-X Gravel Tire’s New Rubber</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"3373a9dd1c63f4c2bdec2280d344f856d5bb79a51fd63112ef24c11ea74a51bd","category":"Cycling"}